Print a caugi

print.Rd

Print a caugi

Arguments

x

A caugi object.

...

Not used.

Value

The input caugi object, invisibly.

See also

Other caugi methods: length()

Examples

cg <- caugi(
  A %-->% B + C,
  nodes = LETTERS[1:5],
  class = "DAG"
)
print(cg)
#> # A tibble: 5 × 1
#>   name 
#>   <chr>
#> 1 A    
#> 2 B    
#> 3 C    
#> 4 D    
#> 5 E    
#> # A tibble: 2 × 3
#>   from  edge  to   
#>   <chr> <chr> <chr>
#> 1 A     -->   B    
#> 2 A     -->   C
